lender.name: We Are One World
lender.loan_because:
What we do:
Many workable adults around the world do not have a chance to create an economic environment that supports them. This is why Michael Karalewich and I have started We Are One World. We Are One World is a nonprofit organization that is committed to providing opportunities to underprivileged people. We believe that in our globalized world it is a moral duty of the privileged to eradicate inequality on a global scale. By giving micro-loans to underworked individuals we will give them a tool to better their own, and their community's lives. Our goal is to alleviate the hardship for them to start a small business by giving them the necessary start-up capital. Many people have profit earning skills, but aren't able to utilize them because of their lack of start-up resources to buy the necessary tools. By investing small amounts of money, we can give them start-up tools of the trade such as a sewing machine. This initial investment will help get their business started. Once their business become profitable they will pay back the loan virtually interest free. This repaid loan will then be reinvested into another individual to do the same, creating a circular effect.
What Volunteers Do:
Anyone can join We Are One World. Volunteers do what they can; we issue no requirements or obligations. Volunteers donate their time and resources however they feel comfortable and suited to them. Normally volunteers voice there opinions on how to make We Are One World better, and participate in our fund raisers trying to raise money. Our officers allocate our money and schedule events to generate funds and awareness.
How It was Created:
We Are One World was created by Semester At Sea students from across the world in combination of Pennsylvania State University students. These students strive for a better world and have created this non-government organization in effort to create more equality across the Globe.
lender.occupational_info: Mission We Are One World has two main goals 1. Create opportunities for economic stability by providing micro-loans. 2. Provide a tool for globally conscious citizens to help raise the quality of life on a global scale. Email weareoneworldngo@gmail.com
